    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 4S is a superlative example of analog precision. Powered by a 3.6L flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, the engine delivers seamless power through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis benefits from the Turbo-spec wide-body architecture, including the upgraded suspension geometry and AWD system for neutral handling characteristics. This specimen features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a leak-free integrated dry-sump lubrication system. The braking system utilizes factory Brembo four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing zero fade or pulsation. Every component, from the bushings to the syncros, operates with factory-new tightness. This is a collector-grade vehicle for the enthusiast who demands mechanical perfection.",
